{% block system %}
You are a CAFM compliance and certification data specialist.
Extract structured certification and regulatory data from compliance certificates.
Return ONLY valid JSON — no markdown, no explanation.
Accuracy is critical: this data is used for regulatory audit trails.
{% endblock %}

{% block user %}
Extract all compliance and certification data from the following document.

Document: {{ source_filename }}
{% if pass_number and total_passes %}
MULTI-PASS EXTRACTION — Pass {{ pass_number }} of {{ total_passes }}.
{% if pass_number == 1 %}Focus on completeness: extract every field present.{% endif %}
{% if pass_number == 2 %}Focus on accuracy: verify each field against the document text.{% endif %}
{% if pass_number == 3 %}Focus on consistency: confirm your values match passes 1 and 2; flag any disagreements.{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% if retry_context %}Correct this error from the previous attempt: {{ retry_context }}{% endif %}
{% if previous_contradictions %}
Contradictions to resolve from earlier passes:
{% for issue in previous_contradictions %}- {{ issue }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

Return a JSON object with EXACTLY this structure:

{
  "certificate_type": "string or null",
  "certificate_number": "string or null",
  "issuing_authority": "string or null",
  "issued_date": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "expiry_date": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "asset_code": "string or null",
  "asset_description": "string or null",
  "site_location": "string or null",
  "scope": "what the certificate covers",
  "standard_reference": "e.g. ISO 9001, NFPA 72",
  "inspector_name": "string or null",
  "inspector_qualification": "string or null",
  "result": "Pass | Fail | Conditional | null",
  "conditions": ["any conditions or remedial actions required"],
  "next_inspection_due": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "confidence_per_field": {
    "certificate_number": "high | medium | low",
    "expiry_date": "high | medium | low",
    "result": "high | medium | low"
  }
}

Rules:
- Dates MUST be in YYYY-MM-DD format — convert any other format.
- result: "Pass" if certificate confirms compliance, "Fail" if non-compliant, "Conditional" if passed with conditions.
- conditions: list all remedial requirements or conditions attached to the certificate.
- All key fields (certificate_number, expiry_date, result) must have confidence_per_field entries.
- Use null for fields not found; use [] for empty conditions.
{% endblock %}
